body:
Hi,

I am trying to update an excel spredsheet which contains football data, but when overwriting data with the codesnippet below, everything runs smoothly and saves. But when I reopen the xlsx file the rows "are gone", but not really, as if i pull down the top row they expand one by one and the data is there. Why is this happening? the code logs out that the row height is 15 at both lines, but i doesnt seem so. Pictures at bottom, trying to explain how i make the data visible.
```javascript
exceljs.ws.eachRow({ includeEmpty: true }, (row, rowNumber) => {
            console.log(row.height);
            row.values = Object.values(data[rowNumber - 2]);
            row.height = 15;
            console.log(Object.values(data[rowNumber - 2]));
            console.log(row.height);
        });

await exceljs.wb.xlsx.writeFile("new.xlsx");
```

