Sorry for the late response, I am currently using v3.7.0, and the bug is still present.

I used this code snippet for testing: 
```javascript
exceljs.ws.eachRow((row, rowNumber) => {
        console.log(row.hidden);
        if (rowNumber < 2 || rowNumber > data.length + 1) return;
        row.values = Object.values(data[rowNumber - 2]);
        console.log(row.hidden);
    });
````

and the output is simply true for all iterations, so it seems like the cells gets a hidden value from a previous action. I actually have to dig deeper into this issue as I cannot put a finger on what exceljs method that is causing this issue to appear. Previous to this method call I set the columns, so I have to debug that function.
